cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.ET, cs.SE, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the software architecture for network stacks on constrained IoT devices, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses functional and non-functional requirements for the software architecture, which could fall under the categories of embedded systems (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a future-proof alternative to existing IoT network stack architectures, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
